Frank A. Riddick IIIChief Executive Officer and Director, FloWorks International, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Frank A. Riddick III, has been Chief Executive Officer of Shale-Inland Holdings, LLC since September 2013. Mr. Riddick has 30 years of experience in a wide range of industrial businesses. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Zekelman Industries Inc. from March 2010 to February 2013. He was previously the Chief Operating Officer at JMC since August 2009. Mr. Riddick served as an Advisor at TowerBrook Capital Partners L.P. He served as the President and Chief ... Executive Officer of Formica Corp. from January 2002 to April 2008 and was instrumental in assisting Formica to emerge from Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings in June 2004. Prior to joining Formica, Mr. Riddick served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Armstrong World Industries, Inc. from February 2000 to November 2001, which he joined in March 1995 and served as its Chief Financial Officer until February 2000. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Armstrong Holdings, Inc. He has served as the Chief Executive Officer of Triangle Pacific Corp. Previously, he worked at General Motors, which he joined in 1980 and where he remained until March 1987, having served as regional treasurer for GM in Brussels. He left GM and joined Merrill Lynch & Co., Inc., where he served as a Treasurer as well as an Investment Banker involved in mergers and acquisitions for the next three years. He served as Controller and Treasurer at FMC Corporation. He served as Regional Treasurer of Motors Liquidation Company. Mr. Riddick served as the Executive Chairman of Shale-Inland Holdings, LLC since February 2013 until September 2013. He serves as a Director of Laminates Acquisition Company and FM Holdings Inc. He serves as a Member of Management Advisory Board at TowerBrook Capital Partners L.P. He has been a Director of JMC Steel Group, Inc. since March 2010. He served as an Independent Director of Geeknet, Inc. from August 20, 2010 to July 17, 2015. He has been an Independent Director at World Wrestling Entertainment Inc., since August 2008. He also serves on the Board of Visitors of the Fuqua School of Business at Duke University. He served as an Independent Director of GrafTech International Limited from September 29, 2004 to May 20, 2010. He served as a Director of Formica Corp. until April 30, 2008. Mr. Riddick received an M.B.A. from Duke University's Fuqua School of Business in 1980 and a B.A. in Mathematics and Economics from Vanderbilt University in 1978.Read Full Background




